originContent: A ray cast based rigid body vehicle system for Godot 4.2 and above
translatedContent: A ray cast based rigid body vehicle system for Godot 4.2 and above

originContent: A physics based vehicle controller designed to play well on a keyboard and be easy to configure. All parameters are contained in one script (vehicle.gd) and tooltips are provided for all of them.
translatedContent: A physics based vehicle controller designed to play well on a keyboard and be easy to configure. All parameters are contained in one script (vehicle.gd) and tooltips are provided for all of them.

originContent: This controller features many systems that assist with making a competent vehicle such as:
translatedContent: This controller features many systems that assist with making a competent vehicle such as:

originContent: - Calculated suspension parameters; proper suspension parameters can be difficult to get right, therefore this controller will calculate spring rates and damping rates based on ratios and weight distribution.
translatedContent: - Calculated suspension parameters; proper suspension parameters can be difficult to get right, therefore this controller will calculate spring rates and damping rates based on ratios and weight distribution.

originContent: - demo_arcade.tscn: Handles similar to an arcade style race car, lots of grip, easy to control, and lots of assists.
translatedContent: - demo_arcade.tscn: Handles similar to an arcade style race car, lots of grip, easy to control, and lots of assists.

originContent: - demo_simcade.tscn: Handles closer to a real car with assists to help keep the car under control.
translatedContent: - demo_simcade.tscn: Handles closer to a real car with assists to help keep the car under control.

originContent: - demo_monster_truck.tscn: Handles like a monster truck, with very little assists.
translatedContent: - demo_monster_truck.tscn: Handles like a monster truck, with very little assists.

originContent: - Steering: Left: ← or a Right: → or d
translatedContent: - Steering: Left: ← or a Right: → or d

originContent: This controller works well in both the Godot and Jolt physics engines. A physics tick rate of at least 120 is recommended and higher values can be used, but note that vehicle behavior will be different when switching tick rates.
translatedContent: This controller works well in both the Godot and Jolt physics engines. A physics tick rate of at least 120 is recommended and higher values can be used, but note that vehicle behavior will be different when switching tick rates.

originContent: Huge thanks to Dechode and Wolfe for sharing their projects to the Godot community. Sharing this project is my way of paying it forward. Portions of this code are based on [Dechode's Godot Advanced Vehicle](https://github.com/Dechode/Godot-Advanced-Vehicle) and [SERIES: Driving Simulator Workshop](https://lupine-vidya.itch.io/gdsim/devlog/677572/series-driving-simulator-workshop-mirror) and attribution is included in the appropriate source files.
translatedContent: Huge thanks to Dechode and Wolfe for sharing their projects to the Godot community. Sharing this project is my way of paying it forward.
